<br>
I plan on starting a new adventurer.<br>
<br>
I was thinking of focusing on MA as my prime fighting skill untill ma &gt; 120<br>
<br>
At that point switching over (or begining to) switch over to 1h edge (hand blades) to multi-wield along with martial arts..<br>
<br>
From what I can read here I would think that should be an easier start for the character (cheaper pre-15 as not having to worry about finding/using a decent weapon to get damage upgrades) and stay functional through out thier life.<br>
<br>
My question are:<br>
<br>
1) Do you all think this would be a functional character?<br>
<br>
2) From what I have read here it sounds like your 'to hit' and 'damage' for your martial arts is based strictly off your attack value (as shown in the charcter info, NOT your MA skill) so once the weapons are equipped (making attack value based off the weapons) there is little need to raise MA if skill is over 120?<br>
<br>
