<br>
Provided that Funcom doesn't change the &quot;punching when wielding weapons&quot; aspect--which I'm strongly convinced they will, despite a near-total lack of evidence--it should work well. Don't know what MA skill is on Adv (isn't it light blue?), but I'm not sure about using MA primarily until it hits 120... that takes a while even for MAs. I think I hit 120 on test with an Opifex MA and buffs (but no implants), around level 20ish. And 2 of my 3 primary stats are green, along with the MA skill itself.<br>
<br>
I'd think going 1he and blading it until you could get the MA up would be a better option, but then you're back to the &quot;gotta find a good wep to be effective&quot; situation. Dunno.<br>
<br>
&quot;2) From what I have read here it sounds like your 'to hit' and 'damage' for your martial arts is based strictly off your attack value (as shown in the charcter info, NOT your MA skill) so once the weapons are equipped (making attack value based off the weapons) there is little need to raise MA if skill is over 120?&quot;<br>
<br>
Your attack effectiveness in any given method (punching = MA, blade = 1he or 2he) depends on your skill in that method. The &quot;Attack&quot; rating displays whatever the skill level is in the weapon you have equipped, unless you have no weapons equipped--then it shows the MA skill.<br>
<br>
Which means if you have a 120 MA skill, you won't be hitting mobs much with your fists over, say, level 30ish, regardless of what your blade skill or Attack rating is... because your MA skill is still 120.<br>
<br>
To put this in perspective, this means when I arm a Squibber and my skill in it is like 30ish, I should never be able to hit with my fists--but the Squibber/1he skill means nothing. Just means I can't see my MA number on the status screen any more. :)<br>
<br>
So... it would be an interesting character, and one different from just about every Adventurer out there--but I'm not sure your points wouldn't be spent elsewhere in light of what your combat effectiveness would be with fists. If that makes any sense.<br>
<br>
Best of luck with whatever you decide. :) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/ulaughingowl2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>laughingOwl2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ninja Wanna-Be</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#660000>(8/23/01 9:18:38 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Seeking Advice: for a new Adventurer</span><hr size=1> Alianna,<br>
